# Database credentials
POSTGRES_USER=helix
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=change_me_in_dot_env
POSTGRES_DB=helixterminator

# Grafana admin password
GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change_me_in_dot_env

# Redis (no auth by default in this compose setup)

# Kafka configuration
KAFKA_BROKERS=kafka:9092

# JWT signing keys — auth-service (private+public), gateway-service +
# billing-service (public only). Leave BOTH unset for local dev bring-up:
# auth-service falls back to a loud-warned ephemeral per-process keypair
# (fine for solo local dev, tokens won't validate across restarts or against
# gateway/billing). Populate both + set ENVIRONMENT=production below for a
# shared/staging compose deployment. NEVER commit a real key — see
# docs/guides/JWT_KEY_PROVISIONING.md for how to generate a keypair.
# ENVIRONMENT=production
# JWT_PRIVATE_KEY=<base64-ed25519-private-key -- see docs/guides/JWT_KEY_PROVISIONING.md>
# JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=<base64-ed25519-public-key -- see docs/guides/JWT_KEY_PROVISIONING.md>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Feature-tier operator credentials (§11.4.10 / §11.4.30). Every value
# below is a REDACTED placeholder — populate the real value ONLY in a
# local, gitignored .env, never in this tracked .env.example file. Every
# variable is verified against the real os.Getenv call that reads it (no
# invented values, §11.4.6); each tier is ALREADY implemented on main and
# honestly reports "not configured" when its variable is unset — no
# fabricated success either way. Full per-tier setup + activation
# checklist: docs/credentials/FEATURE_TIER_SETUP.md
#
# NOTE: docker-compose.yml does not yet pass these through to each
# service's `environment:` block (mirrors the existing, already-
# documented STRIPE_SECRET_KEY gap in docs/guides/BILLING.md) — populating
# them here is necessary but not yet sufficient for a `docker compose up`
# deployment; see docs/credentials/FEATURE_TIER_SETUP.md for the current
# honest status of that gap and how to work around it locally.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Push notifications (FCM + APNs-via-FCM) — notification-service ----
# Read by services/notification-service/internal/delivery/push.go
# (PushConfigFromEnv, push.go:135,141). Unset FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON =>
# every push notification honestly gets status "pending_provider_unconfigured"
# (handler.go:250-253) — never a fabricated "sent".
# FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=<path to a Firebase service-account JSON, e.g. scripts/firebase/secrets/fcm-service-account.json -- generate via scripts/firebase/firebase_setup.sh>
# FCM_PROJECT_ID=<REDACTED -- optional, overrides the project_id embedded in the service-account JSON>

# --- Payments (Stripe) — billing-service --------------------------------
# Read by services/billing-service/internal/billing/env.go
# (NewProviderFromEnv, env.go:41,45). Unset STRIPE_SECRET_KEY => every
# subscription-lifecycle-mutating endpoint honestly responds 501 "payments
# provider not configured" (server.go:91) — never a fabricated "active".
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_REDACTED
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_REDACTED

# --- Email (SMTP) — notification-service --------------------------------
# Read by services/notification-service/internal/delivery/email.go
# (SMTPConfigFromEnv, email.go:55,59,63,71,72). Unset SMTP_HOST => every
# email notification honestly gets status "failed" (handler.go:203-205,
# no delivery attempt is made) — never a fabricated "sent".
# SMTP_HOST=<REDACTED -- e.g. smtp.sendgrid.net, or a local Mailhog/Mailpit sink for dev>
# SMTP_PORT=25
# SMTP_FROM=notifications@localhost
# SMTP_USERNAME=<REDACTED -- optional; leave unset for auth-less dev sinks (Mailhog/Mailpit)>
# SMTP_PASSWORD=<REDACTED -- optional; only used when SMTP_USERNAME is set>

# --- AI / LLM (local HelixLLM tier ONLY) — ai-service -------------------
# Read by services/ai-service/cmd/ai-service/main.go (main.go:90,94). Both
# already have working code-level defaults (a local llama.cpp-compatible
# server at 127.0.0.1:18434) so neither is REQUIRED.
# AI_LOCAL_PROVIDER_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18434/v1/chat/completions
# AI_LOCAL_PROVIDER_MODEL=qwen2.5-1.5b-instruct
#
# HONEST NOTE (§11.4.6 no-guessing): there is NO cloud-LLM (OpenAI/
# Anthropic) tier to configure here. ai-service does not read
# OPENAI_API_KEY / ANTHROPIC_API_KEY or any cloud-provider credential —
# that tier is explicitly Operator-blocked and UNIMPLEMENTED (see
# docs/guides/AI_SERVICE.md "Local-only posture — why the cloud tier is
# off" and docs/CONTINUATION.md). No variable is added here for it.
